message.content:
1. Before Cam broke his right arm, he was able to type 9 words per minute on his phone. This means that in 5 minutes, he would be able to type 45 words (9 x 5).
2. After he broke his arm, he had to use his left hand for a while, and he could only type 6 words per minute. In 5 minutes, he would be able to type 30 words (6 x 5).

So, the difference between the number of words he could type in 5 minutes before and after he broke his arm is 15 words. He was able to type 45 words in 5 minutes before, but after breaking his arm, he could only type 30 words in the same amount of time.
